une.com\">[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2006/11/ana_ortiz_on_ug.html Ana Ortiz on 'Ugly Betty': 'I definitely have a Queens connection']</ref> \n* [[John Ortiz]]{{Snd}} American actor and artistic director/co-founder of LAByrinth Theater Company\n* [[Ronnie Ortiz-Magro]]{{Snd}} American television personality and actor; Italian-American father and Puerto Rican mother\n* [[Lana Parrilla]]{{Snd}} American actress; Sicilian mother and Puerto Rican father\n* [[Rosie Perez]]{{Snd}} American actress; Puerto Rican parents<ref name=\"featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com\"/>\n* [[Miguel Pi\u00f1ero]] (1946\u20131988){{Snd}} Puerto Rican playwright, actor, and co-founder of the [[Nuyorican Poets Caf\u00e9]]; a leading member of the Nuyorican literary movement; died in New York<ref>{{cite news | author=Leslie Bennets | title= Miguel Pinero, Whose Plays Dealt With Life in Prison, Is Dead at 41 | url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=940DE6D71E3EF93BA25755C0A96E948260 | work=The New York Times | date=June 18, 1988 | accessdate=2008-10-26}}</ref>\n* [[Aubrey Plaza]]{{Snd}} American actress, comedian and producer of Puerto Rican and English-Irish descent.\n* [[Carlos Ponce]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican actor, singer, composer and television personality; lived in [[Miami]], [[Florida]]<ref>[http://celebritybabies.people.com/2008/09/21/carlos-ponce/ Celebrity Babaies]</ref>\n* [[Freddie Prinze]] (1954\u20131977){{Snd}} American actor and comedian of Puerto Rican and German descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://freddieprinzejr.com/transcript_stern01.htm |title=Freddie Prinze Jr . com |publisher=Freddieprinzejr.com |accessdate=2010-03-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100308024218/http://www.freddieprinzejr.com/transcript_stern01.htm |archivedate=2010-03-08 }}</ref>\n* [[Freddie Prinze Jr.]]{{Snd}} American actor; son of Freddie Prinze<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/91/Freddie-Jr-Prinze.html |title=Freddie, Jr