icle/0%2C27972%2C101294%2C00.html |date=2011-07-24 }}</ref>\n* [[Lisa Vidal]]{{Snd}} American actress; of Puerto Rican descent<ref>http://www.tv3.co.nz/Lisa-Vidal-as-Christina-Martinez/tabid/1393/articleID/66201/Default.aspx Lisa Vidal (as Christina Martinez){{Snd}} Character Bios</ref>\n* [[Holly Woodlawn]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican-born transgender actress and former Warhol superstar\n* [[David Zayas]]{{Snd}} American theatrical, film, and television actor, ''[[Dexter (TV series)|Dexter]]''; Puerto Rican born and American raised<ref>[http://www.hollywoodpoker.com/green-room/celebrity-poker/biographies/david-zayas.html HollywoodPoker.com:David Zayas]</ref>\n\n== Directors, producer and screenwriters of films, theater and TV ==\n* [[Miguel Arteta]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican film and television director; film ''[[The Good Girl]]''; television series ''[[Six Feet Under (TV series)|Six Feet Under]]''\n* [[Ivonne Bel\u00e9n]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican documentary film director and producer\n*[[Richard Pe\u00f1a]]{{Snd}} American film festival organizer, [[New York Film Festival]]; professor of film studies at [[Columbia University]]\n* [[Tony Taccone]]{{Snd}} American theater director; of Italian and a Puerto Rican descent<ref name=Hurwitt>Hurwitt, Robert (July 5, 2006), [http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2006/07/05/DDGERJNJ4K1.DTL \"Tony Taccone: Riding high on his recent successes, theater veteran has big plans for Berkeley Rep\"]. ''Chronicle Theater Critic''. (accessed 2009-05-18)</ref>\n* [[Joseph Vasquez]] (1962\u20131995){{Snd}} American independent filmmaker\n\n==Singers and musicians==\n===Alphabetized by surname===\n[[File:Marc Anthony 2009 White House.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Marc Anthony]], singer]]\n[[File:TegoCalderon.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Tego Calderon]]]]\n[[File:DaddyYankee.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Daddy Yankee]]]]\n[[File:FatJoeApr2011.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Fat Joe]]]]\n[[File:Jos\u00e9 Feliciano.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Jos\u00e9 Feliciano]]]]\n* [[Princess Nokia]]{{Snd}} American rapper of Puerto Rican descent \n* [[Agallah]], aka \"8-Off the Assassin\" or \"Don Bishop\"{{Snd}} Puerto Rican and Filipino-American rapper; former member of [[The Diplomats]]-affiliated group [[Purple City]] and the group Propain Campaign\n* [[Johnny Albino]] (1919\u20132011){{Snd}} Puerto Rican bolero singer\n* [[Tite Curet Alonso]] (1926\u20132003){{Snd}} composer of over 2,000 salsa songs\n* [[Melanie Amaro]]{{Snd}} American-born [[British Virgin Islands]] singer; won the [[The X Factor (U.S. season 1)|first season]] of ''[[The X Factor (U.S.)|The X Factor USA]]'' in 2011\n* [[Marc Anthony]]{{Snd}} American singer of Puerto Ricans parents<ref>[http://www.urbanlatino.com/feature/57-cover-story/78-marc-anthony Urban Latino: Marc Anthony<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100915014314/http://www.urbanlatino.com/feature/57-cover-story/78-marc-anthony |date=2010-09-15 }}</ref>\n*[[Chucho Avellanet]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican singer of ballads and pop music; son of Adolfo Avellanet\n* [[Manolo Badrena]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican percussionist, known for his work with Weather Report from 1976 to 1977\n* [[Adrienne Bailon]]{{Snd}} American singer and actress; Puerto Rican mother, Ecuadorian father<ref name=\"Douglas Century\">{{cite news|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2006/08/20/fashion/20nite.html?sq=Adrienne%20Bailon&st=nyt&scp=4&pagewanted=all|title= A Song Before Dinner|accessdate= 2008-11-14|author= Douglas Century|date= August 20, 2006|work= New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Lloyd Banks]]{{Snd}} American rapper, member of [[G-Unit]]; of Puerto Rican and African American descent<ref name=\"Sixshot\">{{cite web|title=Lloyd Banks: Hunger for More|url=http://www.sixshot.com/3684/|work=Sixshot|date=June 21, 2004|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080603031648/http://www.sixshot.com/3684/|archivedate=June 3, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[Ray Barretto]] (1929\u20132006){{Snd}} Puerto Rican jazz musician<ref>http://www.salsa-dance-professional.com/ray-barretto.html\nRay Barretto</ref>\n* [[Samuel Ben\u00edquez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican writer, composer, music producer, businessman, publicist, activist, and philanthropist\n* [[Eddie Benitez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican guitarist\n* [[John Benitez]], better known as \"Jellybean Benitez\"{{Snd}} American drummer, guitarist, songwriter, DJ, remixer and music producer; of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Obie Berm\u00fadez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican-American R&B and salsa singer and composer\n* [[Bia (rapper)|BIA]]{{Snd}} American rapper\n* [[Big Daddy Kane]]{{Snd}} American rapper who started his career in 1986 as a member of the rap group the [[Juice Crew]]\n* [[Big Pun]] (1971\u20132000){{Snd}} American rapper; of Puerto Rican descent<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|last=Huey|first=Steve|title=Big Punisher: Biography|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p289921/biography|pure_url=yes}}|website=allmusic|year=2002|accessdate=2008-12-20}}</ref>\n* [[Angela Bofill]]{{Snd}} American R&B vocalist and songwriter; Cuban father, Puerto Rican mother\n* [[Kid Buu (rapper)|Kid Buu]]{{Snd}} American rapper of Puerto Rican and Sicilian descent\n* [[Tego Calder\u00f3n]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican rapper and actor\n* [[Sly Fox (band)|Michael Camacho]]{{Snd}} half of the short-lived [[1980s in music|80s]] dance-pop duo [[Sly Fox (band)|Sly Fox]]; born in [[Los Angeles]], of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Bobby Cap\u00f3]] (1922\u20131989){{Snd}} internationally known singer and songwriter from Puerto Rico; usually combined ballads with classical music\n* [[Irene Cara]]{{Snd}} American singer and actress; of Puerto Rican and Cuban descent<ref>http://www.puertoricanmusictv.com/irene-cara-fame/ Irene Cara \u2013 Fame</ref>\n* [[Kevin Ceballo]]{{Snd}} singer of salsa music of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Chayanne]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican singer; resident of [[Miami]]<ref name=\"informe21\">http://informe21.com/arte-espectaculos/chayanne-nada-imposible-mensaje-estos-tiempos-dificiles Chayanne: \"Nada es Imposible\" es un mensaje para e