a Rosa]]\n* [[Draco Rosa]]{{Snd}} American musician, dancer, singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer and actor\n* [[Willie Rosario]]{{Snd}} musician, composer and Puerto Rican bandleader of salsa music\n* [[Felipe Rose]] (born 1954){{Snd}} American founding member of disco group the [[Village People]]; mother is Puerto Rican, father is Native American\n* [[Frankie Ruiz]] (1958\u20131998){{Snd}} Puerto Rican salsa singer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salsacentro.com/musicdance/music/frankieruiz.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2006-07-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070312143811/http://www.salsacentro.com/musicdance/music/frankieruiz.htm |archivedate=2007-03-12 }} A TRIBUTE TO THE LATE FRANKIE RUIZ (1958\u20131998)</ref>\n* [[Hilton Ruiz]] (1952\u20132006){{Snd}} Puerto Rican American jazz pianist in the Afro-Cuban jazz mold; resident of [[Teaneck, New Jersey]]<ref>Keepnews, Peter. [https://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/07/arts/music/07ruiz.html \"Hilton Ruiz, 54, Pianist Fluent In Jazz and Latin Rhythms\"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', June 7, 2006. Accessed November 4, 2007. \"Hilton Ruiz, a versatile and prolific pianist equally at home in the worlds of modern jazz and Latin music, died yesterday in New Orleans. He was 54 and lived in Teaneck, N.J.\"</ref>\n* [[Sa-Fire]]{{Snd}} American singer\n* [[Jimmy Sabater, Sr.]] (1936\u20132012){{Snd}} American Latin musician; parents were Puerto Rican<ref name=\"Dead\">[http://www.thedeadrockstarsclub.com/2012.html Thedeadrockstarsclub.com]{{Snd}} accessed February 12, 2012</ref>\n* [[Bobby Sanabria]]{{Snd}} American drummer, percussionist, composer, arranger, bandleader, educator, producer, and writer specializing in Latin jazz; of Puerto Rican descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latinjazzclub.com/Bobby_Sanabria.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-02-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120220102521/http://www.latinjazzclub.com/Bobby_Sanabria.h