diquito.com/modules.php?name=News&file=article&sid=26006 |archivedate=2011-09-28 }} El Periodiquito Olga Ta\u00f1\u00f3n se declara en quiebra en Estados Unidos\nDebe m\u00e1s de 7 millones de d\u00f3lares (In Spanish:The Periodiquito: Olga Tanon has filed for bankruptcy in the U.S.\n Owes more than $ 7 million)</ref>\n* [[Juan Tizol]] (1900\u20131984){{Snd}} Puerto Rican trombonist and composer\n* [[Manoella Torres]]{{Snd}} \"the woman who was born to sing\"; American singer and actress; of Puerto Rican descent; resident of Mexico<ref>http://sites.google.com/site/manoellatorres4ever/ MANOELLA TORRES\nLA MUJER QUE NACI\u00d3 PARA CANTAR (In Spanish:MANOELLA TORRES the woman who was born to sing)</ref> \n* [[Tommy Torres]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican producer, singer, and songwriter\n* [[Tony Touch]]{{Snd}} American hip hop break dancer, rapper, DJ, producer and actor; of Puerto Rican descent<ref>http://www.planetafashionmagazine.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=204:tony-touch&catid=41:djas&Itemid=65 Planeta fashion magazine: TONY TOUCH. Retrieved July 20, 2011, to 22:48 pm.</ref>\n* [[Mario Vazquez|Mario V\u00e1zquez]]{{Snd}} pop and R&B American singer; Puerto Rican parents<ref>[http://top40.about.com/od/artistspz/p/mariovazquez.htm Mario Vazquez] from [[About.com]]</ref>\n* [[Alan Vega]]{{Snd}} American vocalist\n* [[Little Louie Vega]]{{Snd}} American musician; half of the Masters At Work musical production team\n* [[Veronica (singer)|Veronica]]{{Snd}} American dance music singer and theatrical actress; parents were Puerto Rican<ref>[http://www.caller2.com/2000/march/12/today/local_ne/2298.html 'Selena Forever' performers prepare for opening night] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120217154956/http://www.caller2.com/2000/march/12/today/local_ne/2298.html |date=2012-02-17 }}</ref>\n* [[Vico C]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican rapper and reggaeton artist; considered one of the founding fathers of reggaeton; influential in the development of Latin American