in-Stokes|La Fountain-Stokes, Lawrence]]. ''Queer Ricans: Cultures and Sexualities in the Diaspora.'' Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press, 2009. {{ISBN|0-8166-4092-0}}</ref>\n* [[Crazy Legs (dancer)|Crazy Legs]]{{Snd}} breakdancer, president of [[Rock Steady Crew]]\n* [[Susie Castillo]]{{Snd}} former beauty queen; held the Miss USA title; competed in the Miss Teen USA and Miss Universe pageants; Dominican father, Puerto Rican mother<ref name=nyp>[http://www.nypost.com/seven/06062007/tempo/my_mass__mania_tempo_susie_castillo.htm Castillo, Susie, \"My 'Mass.' Mania\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221521/http://www.nypost.com/seven/06062007/tempo/my_mass__mania_tempo_susie_castillo.htm |date=2007-09-26 }}, ''[[New York Post]]'' June 6, 2007</ref>\n* [[Carmella DeCesare]]{{Snd}} American model; ''Playboy'' magazine's Miss April 2003 and Playmate of the Year 2004; of Italian and Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Michelle Font]]{{Snd}} beauty queen; Miss Washington USA; competed in the 2008 Miss USA pageant; of Cuban and Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Jaslene Gonzalez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican-American model, Puerto Rican born<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.misquincemag.com/quinceanera-picture-stories/celebrity/jaslene-gonzalez|title = Jaslene Gonzalez|publisher = Mis Quince Magazine| date = February 5, 2008}}</ref> and American raised<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.extranews.net/news.php?nid=2783&clave=a%3A1%3A%7Bi%3A0%3Bs%3A7%3A%22jaslene%22%3B%7D|publisher = Gonzalez Extra Newspaper|title = title|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928075350/http://www.extranews.net/news.php?nid=2783&clave=a%3A1%3A%7Bi%3A0%3Bs%3A7%3A%22jaslene%22%3B%7D|archivedate = 2007-09-28}}</ref>\n* [[Melanie Iglesias]]{{Snd}} American model and actress; of Puerto Rican, Italian, and Filipino heritage<ref>[http://www.worldsmostbeautiful.com/2011/08/05/melanie-iglesias-wild-card/ Wild Card].</ref>\n* [[Danielle Polanco]]{{Snd}} dancer and choreographer; D