/PRSportsBeat0715-en.html |archivedate=2011-10-30 }}</ref>\n* [[Carlos Arroyo]]{{Snd}} professional basketball point guard, last played for the Boston Celtics\n* [[Harry Arroyo]]{{Snd}} American former boxer\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Juan Barea]]{{Snd}} [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] player; Puerto Rican resident of Miami<ref name=\"vocero\">{{cite news| author=Jos\u00e9 R. Ort\u00fazar| url=http://www.vocero.com/noticias.asp?n=80706&s=Deportes| title=Jos\u00e9 Juan Barea se queda en los Mavericks| newspaper=El Vocero| language=Spanish| accessdate=July 27, 2007|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070927180105/http://www.vocero.com/noticias.asp?n=80706&s=Deportes |archivedate = September 27, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Wilfred Ben\u00edtez]]{{Snd}} American boxer\n* [[H\u00e9ctor Camacho]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican professional boxer\n* [[H\u00e9ctor Camacho, Jr.]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican boxer and son of H\u00e9ctor\n* [[Eddie Casiano]]{{Snd}} basketball player; American born and Puerto Rican raised; of Puerto Rican descent<ref>[http://www.lnbp.com.mx/web2/nota.php?idnota=10686 EDDIE CASIANO EL NUEVO ENTRENADOR.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928151908/http://www.lnbp.com.mx/web2/nota.php?idnota=10686 |date=2011-09-28 }}</ref>\n* [[Orlando Cepeda]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican born, American raised\n* [[Julie Chu]]{{Snd}} American Olympic ice hockey player; plays forward on the US women's ice hockey team; Chinese and Puerto Rican <ref>[http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/01/15/Olympic.preview/index.html Vancouver welcomes the world]</ref>\n* [[Roberto Clemente]] (1934\u20131972){{Snd}} Puerto Rican Major League Baseball right fielder; [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum|Hall of Fame]]\n* [[Alex Cora]]{{Snd}} former infielder in Major League Baseball, currently general manager of the Boston Red Sox \n* [[Victor Cruz (American football)|Victor Cruz]]{{Snd}} wide receiver in the NFL\n* [[Guillermo Diaz (basketball)|Guillermo Diaz]]{{Snd}} Puerto 