cial, and law teacher; first Puerto Rican appointed to a federal judgeship in the continental US\n* [[Albert Diaz (judge)|Albert D\u00edaz]]{{Snd}} American judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit; parents are Puerto Rican<ref name=observer_20091009>{{cite news|first=Gary L. |last=Wright |author2=Jim Morrill |title=White House evaluates Diaz for 4th Circuit Court |work=[[Charlotte Observer]] |page=1A |date=October 9, 2009 |accessdate=4 November 2009 |quote= |url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/408/story/992162.html }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n[[File:Nick Estavillo.JPG|thumb|140px|[[Nicholas Estavillo]]]]\n* [[Nicholas Estavillo]]{{Snd}} first Puerto Rican and first Hispanic in the history of the [[NYPD]] to reach the three-star rank of Chief of Patrol<ref name=\"CPtR\">[http://www.vosizneias.com/9325/2007/05/21/new-york-ny-veteran-nypd-chief-of/ New York, NY - Veteran NYPD Chief Of Patrol To Retire]</ref>\n* [[Faith Evans (U.S. Marshal)|Faith Evans]]{{Snd}} Hawaiian-Puerto Rican; first woman to be named U.S. Marshal\n* [[Julio M. Fuentes]]{{Snd}} Circuit Judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit; first Hispanic judge to serve the Third Circuit; Puerto Rican born, American raised<ref>http://www.puertorico-herald.org/issues/vol4n20/PRJurist-en.html</ref>\n* [[Juan Manuel Garc\u00eda Passalacqua]] (1937\u20132010){{Snd}} political commentator, lawyer; Puerto Rican, died in Ohio<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |author= Inter News Service |title= Diversas voces lamentan la muerte de Garc\u00eda Passalacqua |work= |publisher= el nuevo dia |location= |id= |pages= |page= |date= July 3, 2010 |accessdate=2010-01-07 |language=Spanish |url=http://www.elnuevodia.com/lluevenmensajesdedueloporgarciapassalacqua-735231.html}}</ref>\n[[File:Carmen M. Ortiz.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Carmen Ortiz]]]]\n* [[Dora Irizarry]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican federal judge in New York\n* [[Irma Lozada]]{{Snd}} first female police officer to die in action in New York<ref name=\"NYT1\">[https://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/22/nyregion/22slain.html?_r=1 Recalling a Slain Officer, and the Equality of Peril]</ref>\n* [[Jos\u00e9 Mel\u00e9ndez-P\u00e9rez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican-born U.S. Customs and Border Protection Inspector at Orlando International Airport who became a key figure for the 9/11 Commission when he refused entry to an alleged terrorist prior to the September 11, 2001 attacks\n* [[Carmen Ortiz]]{{Snd}} prosecutor attorney, Boston, Massachusetts; American born \n* [[Juan P\u00e9rez-Gim\u00e9nez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican born, U.S. federal judge in [[senior status]]\n* [[Roberto A. Rivera-Soto]]{{Snd}} Associate Justice of the New Jersey Supreme Court; American born, Puerto Rican raised\n* [[Vanessa Ruiz]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican associate Judge of the District of Columbia Court of Appeals, the highest court for the District of Columbia<ref>[https://www.oyez.org/cases/1980-1989/1981/1981_80_988/ Oyez: Havens Realty Corp. v. Coleman, 455 U.S. 363 (1982), U.S. Supreme Court Case Summary & Oral Argument<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n* [[Benito Romano]]{{Snd}} first American of Puerto Rican heritage to hold the US Attorney's post in New York on an interim basis\n* [[Joe S\u00e1nchez]]{{Snd}} American highly decorated former New York City police officer; author whose books give an insight as to the corruption within the department; parents are Puerto Rican<ref name=\"NYDN\">[http://www.nydailynews.com/ny_local/bronx/2008/07/16/2008-07-16_fired_nypd_cop_writes_gritty_book_to_set.html Fired NYPD cop writes gritty book to set record straight, BY John Marzulli]</ref>\n* [[Sonia Maria Sotomayor]]{{Snd}} Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the U.S. since August 2009; the Court's 111th justice, its first Hispanic justice, and its third female justice<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abclocal.go.com/wabc/story?section=news/politics&id=6831739 |title=Judge Sonia Sotomayor bio. |accessdate=July 26, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090528000356/http://abclocal.go.com/wabc/story?section=news%2Fpolitics&id=6831739 |archive-date=May 28, 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Edgardo Ramos]]{{Snd}}  United States District Judge of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York since 2011.\n* [[Edwin Torres (judge)|Edwin Torres]]{{Snd}} New York state supreme court judge and author; parents are Puerto Rican<ref name=\"herald\">{{cite news|url=http://www.puertorico-herald.org/issues/vol4n48/ProfTorres-en.html |title=Puerto Rico Profile: Judge Edwin Torres |date=2000-12-01 |publisher=Puerto Rico Herald |accessdate=2007-11-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080106172450/http://www.puertorico-herald.org/issues/vol4n48/ProfTorres-en.html |archivedate=2008-01-06 }}</ref>\n* [[Juan R. Torruella]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican jurist; currently a judge on the U.S. Court of Appeals for the First Circuit; first and to date only Hispanic to serve in that court\n\n== Military ==\n[[File:ADM Rivero, Horacio Jr.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Horacio Rivero, Jr.]]]]\n[[File:Carmen Conteras Bozak.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Carmen Contreras-Bozak]]]]\n[[File:Felices se.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Salvador E. Felices]]]]\n[[File:Virgil R. Miller.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Virgil R. Miller]]]]\n[[File:Maritza Ryan.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Maritza S\u00e1enz Ryan]]]]\n* [[Domingo Arroyo, Jr.]] (1971\u20131993){{Snd}} U.S. Marine; first Puerto Rican and American serviceman killed in Operation Restore Hope during the Somalian Civil War; his family moved to the US when he was 14, seeking better living conditions\n* [[Joseph B. Aviles, Sr.|Joseph B. Avil\u00e9s]] (1897\u20131990){{Snd}} served in the U.S. Navy and later in the Coast Guard; in 1925, became the first Hispanic Chief Petty Officer in the US Coast Guard; Puerto Rican, lived in Maryland<ref>[http://www.interment.net/data/search-usa-maryland.htm?cx=partner-pub-1928517298809652%3Ae1kcewlu31x&cof=FORID%3A10&ie=ISO-8859-1&q=Joseph+B.+Aviles&sa=Search Baltimore National Cemetery]</ref>\n* [[Rafael Celestino Ben\u00edtez]] (1917\u20131999){{Snd}} highly decorated submarine commander who led the rescue effort of the crew members of the USS ''Cochino'' during the Cold War\n* [[Jos\u00e9 M. Cabanillas]] (1901\u20131979){{Snd}} Puerto Rican executive Officer of the USS ''Texas'', which participated in the invasions of North Africa and the Battle of Normandy (D-Day) during [[World War II]]; died in [[Virginia]]\n* [[Iv\u00e1n Castro]]{{Snd}} U.S. Army officer who has continued serving on active duty in the Special Forces despite losing his eyesight; parents are Puerto Rican<ref name=nr>{{cite magazine |title=Captain Extraordinary |author=Nordlinger, Jay |magazine=[[National Review]] |date=2009-02-09 |volume=61 |issue=2 |pages=16\u201317|author-link=Jay Nordlinger }}</ref>\n* [[Richard Carmona]]{{Snd}} American physician and public health administrator<ref>http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local_news/article/Obesity-called-a-threat-to-U-S-security-845630.php Obesity called a threat to US security</ref>\n* [[Carmen Contreras-Bozak]] (born 1919){{Snd}} first Hispanic to serve in the U.S. Women's Army Corps, where she served as an interpreter and in numerous administrative positions; Puerto Rican; lives in Tampa, Florida<ref name=\"WAC\">[http://www.utopia.utexas.edu/explore/latino/narratives/07Bozak_Carmen.html Young woman's life defined by service in Women's Army Corp] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060919122433/http://utopia.utexas.edu/explore/latino/narratives/07Bozak_Carmen.html |date=2006-09-19 }}</ref>\n* [[Linda Garcia Cubero|Linda Garc\u00eda Cubero]]{{Snd}} former U.S. Air Force officer; of Mexican-American-Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Ruben A. Cubero|Rub\u00e9n A. Cubero]]{{Snd}} highly decorated member of the U.S. Air Force; first Hispanic graduate of the US Air Force Academy to be named Dean of the Faculty of the academy; parents were Puerto Rican<ref name=\"AF\">[htt