.poptower.com/amaury-nolasco.htm {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090809121025/http://www.poptower.com/amaury-nolasco.htm |date=2009-08-09 }}\nAmaury Nolasco{{Snd}} Amaury Nolasco Pictures, Biography, Dating. Retrieved on July 26, 2011, to 21:41 pm.</ref>\n* [[Miguel A. N\u00fa\u00f1ez Jr.]]{{Snd}} American actor of Puerto Rican and Dominican descent<ref name=tango>[http://dr1.com/articles/dominican_american.shtml], Dominican Americans</ref>\n* [[Karen Olivo]]{{Snd}} American actress; of [[People of the Dominican Republic|Dominican]], Puerto Rican, [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Native American]], and [[Chinese people|Chinese]] descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/exclusive-tony-award-winner-karen-olivo-shares-her-story|title=Tony Award Winner Karen Olivo Shares Her Story|author=Laura Checkoway|work=latina.com|date=June 9, 2009|accessdate=January 12, 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Ana Ortiz]]{{Snd}} American actress and singer; of Puerto Rican and Irish descent<ref name=\"featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com\">[http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/entertainment_tv/2006/11/ana_ortiz_on_ug.html Ana Ortiz on 'Ugly Betty': 'I definitely have a Queens connection']</ref> \n* [[John Ortiz]]{{Snd}} American actor and artistic director/co-founder of LAByrinth Theater Company\n* [[Ronnie Ortiz-Magro]]{{Snd}} American television personality and actor; Italian-American father and Puerto Rican mother\n* [[Lana Parrilla]]{{Snd}} American actress; Sicilian mother and Puerto Rican father\n* [[Rosie Perez]]{{Snd}} American actress; Puerto Rican parents<ref name=\"featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com\"/>\n* [[Miguel Pi\u00f1ero]] (1946\u20131988){{Snd}} Puerto Rican playwright, actor, and co-founder of the [[Nuyorican Poets Caf\u00e9]]; a leading member of the Nuyorican literary movement; died in New York<ref>{{cite news | author=Leslie Bennets | title= Miguel Pinero, Whose Plays Dealt With Life in Prison, Is Dead at 41 | url=https://query.nytime