e-en/biography|title=Biography \u2013 The Official Alexis Jordan Site |publisher=Official Alexis Jordan Site |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110215120612/http://www.alexisjordanofficial.com/be-en/biography |url-status=dead|archivedate=February 15, 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Kelis]]{{Snd}} American musical artist; father is African-American, mother is of half Puerto Rican descent<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/artists/kelis |title=Kelis &#124; MTV UK |publisher=Mtv.co.uk |accessdate=2011-02-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110904003131/http://www.mtv.co.uk/artists/kelis |archivedate=2011-09-04 }}</ref>\n* [[Tori Kelly]] \u2013 singer father is Puerto Rican and Jamaican descent<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=168s&v=vZwmsx4YLQk|title=Tori Kelly Discusses the BET Awards, Not Being White + Dreaming of a Grammy on Ebro in the AM (2:48)|accessdate=July 1, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Kurious]]{{Snd}} American hip hop artist; of Puerto Rican and Cuban descent<ref>http://www.ohhla.com/anonymous/kurious/monkey/walklike.kur.txt</ref>\n* [[George Lamond]]{{Snd}} American freestyle music singer, of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[H\u00e9ctor Lavoe]] (1946\u20131993){{Snd}} Puerto Rican singer, resident of New York<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldmusic.nationalgeographic.com/worldmusic/view/page.basic/artist/content.artist/hector_lavoe |title=H\u00e9ctor Lavoe: National Geographic Music |accessdate=2007-06-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070624223629/http://worldmusic.nationalgeographic.com/worldmusic/view/page.basic/artist/content.artist/hector_lavoe |archivedate=2007-06-24 }}</ref>\n* [[Manny Lehman (disc jockey)|Manny Lehman]]{{Snd}} American house music DJ and producer\n* [[Lil Suzy]]{{Snd}} half Italian, half Puerto Rican American Latin freestyle, pop- and dance-music singer\n* [[Toby Love]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican American singer-songwriter; Puerto Rican parents\n* [[Lumidee]]{{Snd}} American singer-songwrit