point]]; American born, father is Puerto Rican, lived on the island as a teenager. Father served in US Army in Korea and Vietnam\n* [[Robbie Rivera]]{{Snd}} DJ producer\n* [[Chino Rodriguez|Chino Rodr\u00edguez]] (born 1954){{Snd}} music producer, band leader, musician, manager, booking agent, record company executive, business consultant, and American record label owner, specializing in [[Latin music (genre)|Latin music]], most notably [[Salsa music|salsa]] and [[Latin jazz]]; American-born, of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Daniel Rodr\u00edguez (tenor)]]{{Snd}} American operatic tenor from New York City\n* [[Tito Rodr\u00edguez]] (1923\u20131973){{Snd}} Puerto Rican singer and bandleader, known as \"El inolvidable\"<ref name=\"MOPR\">[http://www.musicofpuertorico.com/index.php/artists/tito_rodriguez/ Music of Puerto Rico]</ref>\n* [[Omar Rodr\u00edguez-L\u00f3pez]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican singer and musician lead guitar for [[At the Drive-In]] and [[Mars Volta]]\n[[File:Concierto de Gilberto Santa Rosa en Pi\u00f1as.jpg|thumb|140px|Gilberto Santa Rosa]]\n* [[Draco Rosa]]{{Snd}} American musician, dancer, singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer and actor\n* [[Willie Rosario]]{{Snd}} musician, composer and Puerto Rican bandleader of salsa music\n* [[Felipe Rose]] (born 1954){{Snd}} American founding member of disco group the [[Village People]]; mother is Puerto Rican, father is Native American\n* [[Frankie Ruiz]] (1958\u20131998){{Snd}} Puerto Rican salsa singer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salsacentro.com/musicdance/music/frankieruiz.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2006-07-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070312143811/http://www.salsacentro.com/musicdance/music/frankieruiz.htm |archivedate=2007-03-12 }} A TRIBUTE TO THE LATE FRANKIE RUIZ (1958\u20131998)</ref>\n* [[Hilton Ruiz]] (1952\u20132006){{Snd}} Puerto Rican American jazz pianist in the Afro-Cuban jazz mold; resident of [[Teaneck, New Jersey]]<ref>Keepnews, Peter.