iano]]{{Snd}} basketball player; American born and Puerto Rican raised; of Puerto Rican descent<ref>[http://www.lnbp.com.mx/web2/nota.php?idnota=10686 EDDIE CASIANO EL NUEVO ENTRENADOR.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928151908/http://www.lnbp.com.mx/web2/nota.php?idnota=10686 |date=2011-09-28 }}</ref>\n* [[Orlando Cepeda]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican born, American raised\n* [[Julie Chu]]{{Snd}} American Olympic ice hockey player; plays forward on the US women's ice hockey team; Chinese and Puerto Rican <ref>[http://www.cnn.com/2010/WORLD/americas/01/15/Olympic.preview/index.html Vancouver welcomes the world]</ref>\n* [[Roberto Clemente]] (1934\u20131972){{Snd}} Puerto Rican Major League Baseball right fielder; [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum|Hall of Fame]]\n* [[Alex Cora]]{{Snd}} former infielder in Major League Baseball, currently general manager of the Boston Red Sox \n* [[Victor Cruz (American football)|Victor Cruz]]{{Snd}} wide receiver in the NFL\n* [[Guillermo Diaz (basketball)|Guillermo Diaz]]{{Snd}} Puerto Rican professional basketball player; [[National Basketball Association|NBA]]\n[[File:Sunny Garcia Xcel Pro 2007 Sunset Beach.jpg|thumb|140px|[[Sunny Garcia]]]]\n* [[Homicide (wrestler)|Nelson Erazo]]{{Snd}} American professional wrestler, better known by his ring name \"Homicide\"; of Puerto Rican descent\n* [[Justin Fargas]]{{Snd}} American football running back; free agent in the NFL; son of [[Antonio Fargas]]\n* [[Sunny Garcia]]{{Snd}} American professional surfer\n* [[Herbert Lewis Hardwick]], aka \"Cocoa Kid\" (1914\u20131966){{Snd}} boxer, inducted into the International Boxing Hall of Fame in 2012; born in Puerto Rico; Puerto Rican mother, African American father<ref>[http://www.ibhof.com/pages/about/inductees/modern/kid_cocoa.html Boxing Hall of Fame]</ref>\n* [[James Chico Hernandez|James \"Chico\" Hernandez]]{{Snd}} American Sambo athlete; a seven-time member of the USA National Team\n* [[Oscar Hern\u00e1ndez (musician)|