_110815/|archive-date=2011-08-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2011, a total of 80 million cars and commercial vehicles were built, led by China, with 18.4 million motor vehicles manufactured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greencarreports.com/news/1074667_80-million-vehicles-built-globally-last-year--a-new-record|title=80 Million Vehicles Built Globally Last Year - A New Record |author=John Voelcker|publisher=Green Car Reports|date=2012-03-29|accessdate=2012-03-29}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! #\n! Country or region\n! Motor vehicles<br/>per 1,000 people\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Total\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Year\n|-\n| 1 || {{flag|San Marino}}|| 1,263\n| ||2013<ref name=\"WorldBank\">{{cite web|url=http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/IS.VEH.NVEH.P3|title=World Bank Data: Motor vehicles (per 1,000 people)|publisher=[[The World Bank]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140209114811/http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/IS.VEH.NVEH.P3|archivedate=February 9, 2014|accessdate=2014-02-09|url-status=dead}} Archived.</ref>\n|-\n| 2 || {{flag|Monaco}}|| 899 \n| ||2013<ref name=\"WorldBank\" />\n|-\n| 3 || {{flag|New Zealand}}|| 860\n|4,240,000\n| 2018<ref>[https://www.mia.org.nz/Sales-Data/Vehicle-Sales]</ref>\n|-\n| 4 || {{flag|United States}}|| 838\n|272,480,899<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/policyinformation/statistics/2017/mv1.cfm|title=Highway Statistics 2017|access-date=2019-05-20}}</ref>|| 2017\n|-\n| 5 || {{flag|Iceland}}|| 824\n|278,924<ref name=\"ceicdata.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/vehicles-statistics-guidance|title=total no of vehicles|website=Gov.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hagstofa.is/media/51192/iceland_in_figures_2018.pdf|title=Iceland in figures 2018|access-date=2019-05-20}}</ref>|| 2016\n|-\n| 6 || {{flag|Liechtenstein}}|| 773 \n| || 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/statistics-explained/index.php?title=Passenger_cars_in_the_EU|title=Passenger cars 